      • make

        private java.lang.String make
        The make field references a String object that holds the make of the car in capital, small or mix letter such as "KIA", "Honda", "Toyota" , "FORD", "Audi", "MazDA" ,"Nissan",... note: all of these word variations "KIA", "kia", "Kia", "KIa" , "kiA","kIA",..etc indicate that the vehicle is make "KIA". default make is "Toyota"

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo​(Vehicle other)
        Compares this vehicle to the specified vehicle. The result is the equal to the difference this vehicle price value - other vehicle price value.
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<Vehicle>
        Parameters:
        other - a vehicle to compare
        Returns:
        a positive value if the price value of this vehicle is greater than the price value of the other vehicle, a negative value if the price value of this vehicle is less than the price value of the other vehicle, or zero if both vehicles have equal price values.
